  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As a validator, I want to be able to set the `graffiti` field in blocks that I propose. \r\n\r\nThe graffiti field is an optional feature allowing validators to set arbitrary data in block proposals. Teku currently has it [hardcoded to all zeros](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/81deceb0070d240768fe3a43fa833fbb3604e9e2/ethereum/datastructures/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/teku/datastructures/blocks/BeaconBlockBody.java#L75).\r\n\r\nIt would be a nice feature to be able to set this per validator from the command line on start up. A stretch goal would be to allow this to be changed via the API in a running validator.\r\n\r\nAs a very minimum it should default to the current version of Teku if not set by the user.",
