    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "At some stage it'd be ideal to be able to set per validator, but after talking with Ben, he's happy to have graffiti passed in via command line or config file.\n\nIn Prysm it takes any string, so our command line should probably take any string data, and convert that to byte data for the graffiti.\n\nWe will accept a UTF-8 string, and byte encode it to produce the graffiti.\n\nconcrete example:\n`teku --graffiti=\"The quick brown fox\"`\n\nfailure example (too long):\n`teku --graffiti=\"The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog\"`\n",
